@{
    ViewBag.Title = "Privacy Policy";
}

<div class="page-header">
    <div class="container">
        <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
        <p>Last updated: May 2026</p>
    </div>
</div>

<div class="container py-5">
    <div class="row justify-content-center">
        <div class="col-lg-8">
            <div class="prose-card">

                <p>
                    FakeScope ("we", "us", or "our") is committed to protecting your privacy.
                    This policy explains what data we collect when you use this application and how it is used.
                </p>

                <h2>1. Data We Collect</h2>
                <p>When you submit an article for analysis, we store the following information in our database:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>The article text or URL you submitted</li>
                    <li>Extracted metadata (title, author, publisher, publication date)</li>
                    <li>The AI verdict and confidence score</li>
                    <li>The timestamp of the analysis</li>
                </ul>
                <p>We do <strong>not</strong> collect personal identification information such as your name, email address, or IP address.</p>

                <h2>2. How We Use Your Data</h2>
                <ul>
                    <li>To return analysis results to you in the same session</li>
                    <li>To maintain an audit trail of model predictions for quality improvement</li>
                    <li>To aggregate anonymous usage statistics (e.g., total articles analyzed)</li>
                </ul>

                <h2>3. Data Storage</h2>
                <p>
                    All analysis data is stored in an Apache Cassandra database hosted on our infrastructure.
                    Data is retained for a maximum of 12 months before being automatically purged.
                    We do not sell, rent, or share stored article data with third parties.
                </p>

                <h2>4. External Services</h2>
                <p>
                    When you submit a URL, our server fetches the page on your behalf. The target website
                    may log our server's IP address. We have no control over third-party websites' data practices.
                </p>
                <p>
                    Article content is sent to our internal Python ML microservice for classification.
                    This service runs on the same infrastructure and does not share data externally.
                </p>

                <h2>5. Cookies</h2>
                <p>
                    FakeScope uses only the session cookie required for CSRF protection (anti-forgery token).
                    No tracking cookies or third-party analytics cookies are set.
                </p>

                <h2>6. Your Rights</h2>
                <p>
                    Because we do not collect personally identifiable information, we cannot identify
                    which submissions belong to you. If you have concerns about data stored from a
                    specific analysis, please contact us with the Analysis ID shown on your result page.
                </p>

                <h2>7. Changes to This Policy</h2>
                <p>
                    We may update this policy from time to time. The "Last updated" date at the top of
                    this page will reflect any changes. Continued use of FakeScope after changes
                    constitutes acceptance of the revised policy.
                </p>

                <h2>8. Contact</h2>
                <p>
                    For any privacy-related questions, please open an issue on our project repository
                    or reach out through the contact information provided in the application documentation.
                </p>

            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
